'''Allelotype''' describes the occurrence of an [[allele]] in a [[population]].<ref>{{cite web|title=allelo-, allel- | url=http://wordinfo.info/unit/82 | website=English-Word Information | accessdate=24 Aug 2014}}</ref> Specifically, it describes the [[frequency distribution]] of a given set of alleles in a population.<ref>{{cite web|title=Word Info|url=http://wordinfo.info/unit/82|accessdate=30 May 2014}}</ref> Allelotype is important for the field of [[population genetics]], particularly when studying complex or multifactorial disorders such as cancer. Determining tumor allelotypes increases the understanding of the underlying tumorigenesis and improves the prognosis in tumor patients.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Vogelstein|first=B|title=Allelotype of colorectal carcinomas|journal=Science|date=Apr 14, 1989|volume=244|issue=4901|pages=207–11|doi=10.1126/science.2565047|pmid=2565047|url=https://www.sciencemag.org/content/244/4901/207|accessdate=30 May 2014}}</ref>
