'''''Oryx''''' is a [[peer-review]]ed [[academic journal]] of [[Conservation movement|conservation]] published quarterly by [[Cambridge University Press]] on behalf of [[Fauna & Flora International]]. The journal was established in 1904 as ''Journal of the Society for the Preservation of the Wild Fauna of the Empire'', and is currently edited by [[Martin Fisher (zoologist)|Martin Fisher]]. The named changed to ''Journal of the Society for the Preservation of the Fauna of the Empire'', and acquired its current name in 1950.
