'''Ponnuraj Karthe''' is an Indian structural biologist and a professor and the head of the Department of Crystallography and Biophysics of the [[University of Madras]].<ref name="Faculty profile">{{Cite web |url=http://www.unom.ac.in/index.php?route=department/department/profile&deptid=23&facultyid=79 |title=Faculty profile |date=2018-01-25 |website=University of Madras |access-date=2018-01-25}}</ref> He is known for his research in the fields of structural biology and [[Drug design|drug designing]].<ref name="Department profile">{{Cite web |url=http://www.unom.ac.in/index.php?route=department/department/faculty&deptid=23 |title=Department profile |date=2018-01-25 |website=University of Madras |access-date=2018-01-25}}</ref> His studies have been documented by way of a number of articles<ref name="On ResearchGate">{{Cite web |url=https://www.researchgate.net/scientific-contributions/2064117303_Ponnuraj_Karthe |title=On ResearchGate |date=2018-01-20 |publisher=On ResearchGate |access-date=2018-01-20}}</ref> {{Refn|group=note|Please see ''Selected bibliography'' section}} and [[Google Scholar]], an online repository of scientific articles has listed 46 of them.<ref name="On Google Scholar">{{Cite web |url=https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=CDauvcUAAAAJ&hl=en |title=On Google Scholar |date=2018-01-20 |publisher=Google Scholar |access-date=2018-01-20}}</ref> Besides, he has contributed chapters to books edited by others<ref name="VijayanKolaskar1999">{{cite book|author1=M. Vijayan|author2=A. S. Kolaskar|title=Perspectives in Structural Biology: A Volume in Honour of G.N. Ramachandran|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xTy_M3B5sf4C&pg=PR8|year=1999|publisher=Universities Press|isbn=978-81-7371-254-8|pages=8–}}</ref> and has delivered invited speeches at many seminars<ref name="INPEC2017">{{Cite web |url=http://www.jcbose.ac.in/conference/17/inpec/speakers.html |title=INPEC2017 |date=2018-01-24 |website=www.jcbose.ac.in |access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref> which include the ''Workshop on Advances in Computer Aided Drug Design'' held in August 2010 at the University of Madras.<ref name="Workshop on Advances in Computer Aided Drug Design">{{Cite web |url=http://www.vlifesciences.com/aboutus/newsevents_2010/progam_schedule.pdf |title=Workshop on Advances in Computer Aided Drug Design |date=August 2010 |website=vLife |access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref> He was a member of the national organizing committee of the ''Annual Conference of Indian Biophysical Society'' -
''Molecular Architecture, Dynamics and Assem'', organized by [[Saha Institute of Nuclear Physics]]<ref name="Past Conferences">{{Cite web |url=http://www.saha.ac.in/web/sinp-past-conference?c_id=32&cpage_id=37 |title=Past Conferences |date=2018-01-24 |website=www.saha.ac.in |language=en-gb |access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref> and serves as a member of the national committee of the International Union for Pure and Applied Biophysics (IUPAB)<ref name="International Union for Pure and Applied Biophysics">{{Cite web |url=https://insaindia.res.in/com.php |title=International Union for Pure and Applied Biophysics |date=2018-01-24 |website=insaindia.res.in |access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref> as well as the executive council of the ''Bioinformatics and Drug Discovery Society'' (BIDDS), a non governmental organization promoting dissemination of knowledge in the fields of bioinformatics, biological sciences and other life sciences.<ref name="BIDDS Members">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bidds.org/ec.html |title=BIDDS Members |date=2018-01-24 |website=www.bidds.org |access-date=2018-01-24}}</ref> The [[Department of Biotechnology]] of the Government of India awarded him the [[National Bioscience Award for Career Development]], one of the highest Indian science awards, for his contributions to biosciences, in 2010.<ref name="Awardees of National Bioscience Awards for Career Development">{{Cite web |url=http://dbtindia.nic.in/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/list_of_bioscience_awardees.pdf |title=Awardees of National Bioscience Awards for Career Development |date=2016 |publisher=Department of Biotechnology |access-date=2017-11-20}}</ref>

